<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-158-182 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 690 713</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Computing  May 7 1991 v2 n10 p3(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Professional Press Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Alliance update. (User Alliance for Open Systems) (News)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     User Alliance for Open SystemsConferences and MeetingsOpen SystemsUser NeedsUser Groups.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Alliance UpdateandM;The User Alliance for Open Systems has deemed that its recent meeting held inDallas, Texas was a resounding success.andP;  It was the first meeting convenedsubsequent to the Alliance joining the Corporation for Open Systems (COS).andO;Attendees included users from various industry segments as well asgovernmental agencies and universities.andM;As part of the meeting, four ongoing working groups were created.andP;  Theirmandates are: establishing a process for user requirements; educating on opensystems benefits; building a framework for open systems business cases; anddesigning a framework for open systems technologies.andP;  Additional activitiesincluded preparing the final wording for the charter and the by-laws of theUser Alliance.andM;The next event will be in Vancouver next week, May 15 to 17.andO;</TEXT></DOC>